<br>
As you zone in you will be in a canyon of sorts.  This is the beginning of a series of 'canyons' that run through out the whole zone.  <br>
<br>
To the left of the ent is a camp of grol baku &lt;insert word here&gt;.  They look like boglings.  They are all blue to me and since they were spread out i figured, i am a druid, i can quad-kite.  Well I snare one, turn snare another, then i get rooted.  See apparently these guys have this little thing with the earth, so the ground grabbed me and let me sit there while the Grol Baku warriors played pin the fist on the wood elf.  I lived but barely.  I left the camp and moved on.  Tracking shows a whole slew of con levels from blue-red in a good mix, which for me is a good sign of a zone to level in.  There are lightcrawlers here, scarlet cheetahs (yes they run REALLY REALLY fast), grol baku guys, trol jeg guys, and sun reverants, and bloodthirsty guys.  grol baku and tol jeg are on opposite faction.  you kil a grol and you lose faction with 4 of the bogling looking creatures and gain with trol jeg, and vica versa.  the lightcrawlers are just like every other lightcrawler, they hit kinda hard and blind.   The cheetahs SUCK!  they hit hard, run fast even snared and have a arse load of hp's.  Along the zone wall is aoubt 10 caves give or take which all have blood thirsty warriors or shamans, except for the ones that go to the grey and greig's end.  The blood thirsty guys are realy hungry.  i think wood elf blood is a delecacy because they have a HUGH agro radius and they all came after me.  The sun reverants look likes masked bandits (kinda like rondite bandits in fungus grove)  and they walk funny.  They hit like MOFO's and have a cure of the sun reverant they put on you, its a nasty dot amoungst other things.  These guys range from 35-60.  the 60 onse are on a high 'butte' to use the geographically correct term.  there is a winding path to the top.  Besides what i have listed the zone has no really 'ewww ahh' value.  Gret place to xp, but you need a chanter as adds can be a problem. <p>Greystone Thorngage 39 Druid <BR>
Roundtom Birglechirp Warrior 16 <BR>
